Cell.Text: [S] Ulfric's right-hand man, Galmar Stonefist, has located what he believes is the final resting place of the Jagged Crown. | We're going to make sure he doesn't get his hands on it. | The rest of my men are already assembling outside Korvanjund. I'll meet you there as soon as I finish up here.
General Tullius told me to report to you.
[S] Welcome to the Legion, auxiliary. Listen up.

Node.Caption: MQ103RikkeIntroTopic: I'm ready for my first assignment.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Follow me.
G|<<Shared>> Take that crown back to Solitude, soldier.
G|<<Shared>> Get the crown already. We don't need to hang around here any longer than necessary.
G|<<Shared>> The crown should be around here somewhere. Spread out, and keep your eyes open.
G|The Stormcloaks are here in force. Stick close and follow orders so we don't stir up the whole place against us.
S|Looks like the damned rebels got here first. No matter, we have the element of surprise. Prepare to move out.
You ready, auxiliary?
G|This isn't a damn summer picnic! Hurry up. We need to hit them before they know we're here.

Node.Caption: MQ103RikkeAtKorvanjundWait: Hold on, I need a minute.

Cell.Text: That's what I like to hear. I'll get the full report from Legate Rikke. Now then...
That's not for you to decide. Soldier. | I wouldn't have sent you in the first place if it wasn't going to be worth it. Now then...

Node.Caption: MQ103TulliusBookA2: We lost a lot of good men. I hope it was worth it.

Cell.Text: Yes. Well, I didn't respond as quickly to the Legate's suggestion as perhaps I should have. | But at least we ended up with the damn crown. Now then...

Node.Caption: MQ103TulliusBookA3: The Stormcloaks were there ahead of us.

Cell.Text: Excellent work, soldier. I have to admit, I had my doubts it even existed. Did you run into any trouble?

Node.Caption: MQ103TulliusRetrieveBookTopic: Here's the Jagged Crown. Legate Rikke sent me to deliver it to you.

Cell.Text: [S] Good to see you, my friend! I knew you'd make a proper Legionnaire. | I'm glad you'll be with me in there. I don't like the looks of this place... and I'm not talking about the Stormcloaks.

[S] I remember you... You were with us at Helgen... I heard you came around and picked the right side. Welcome to the Legion! | I'm glad you're with us. I don't like the looks of this place... and I'm not talking about the Stormcloaks.
These old ruins... They don't want us here, the ancient ones. Better left alone.
G|But never mind all that. We're the Emperor's soldiers. We'll do our duty no matter what stands in our way, right?
You, too, huh? I'd much rather a straight up fight than creeping around a place like this.

Node.Caption: MQ103HadvarIntroA2: I know what you mean about these old ruins.

Cell.Text: GS|You must be the new recruit. Welcome to the Legion.
G|At least we got the damn crown. I hope it was worth it.
G|I wish the Legate would let us clear out of here. Place gives me the creeps.
G|I don't know what we're doing here, but orders are orders.
G|I keep thinking I see something moving in the shadows...
G|I hope we don't run into anything worse than Stormcloaks in here.
G|It's the waiting that gets me.
G|I don't like the look of this place.
G|Nobody allowed in. Ulfric Stormcloak's orders. Consider yourself warned.

Are you now? You were at Helgen, one of the prisoners. Although no one seems to know how you got mixed up in that affair. | Normally, I would have welcomed someone like you -- resourceful, clearly no friend of the Empire. | But I've had some disturbing reports of you... seen talking to General Tullius in Castle Dour, for example. | So what do you have to say for yourself? How can I be sure you're not an Imperial spy?

Node.Caption: MQ103UlfricBookTopic: I'm here to join your fight against the Empire.

Cell.Text: So you as good as admit you're working for the Imperials. Yet you walk in here, and ask to join me. What are you playing at?
G|The Imperials wouldn't have just let you walk away. Remember that.

[S] G|You're not short of guts, are you? What's your game? | Why would Tullius waste resources getting the crown only to give it to me? Poisoned perhaps? No. He's not that cunning. | Alright. I believe you. You aren't the first to turn away from the Empire in disgust. | But remember - you're one of us now, forever. Whatever Imperial loyalties you may have had... that's all in the past, forgotten. | Now, to prove yourself to me, I have a task for you. Take my axe, and deliver it to the Jarl of Whiterun.

Node.Caption: MQ103AUlfricBookB1: I made a mistake. I want to be a Stormcloak. The crown belongs to you.

Cell.Text: A legendary crown, dating back to King Harald's time, or before. A powerful relic of a golden age, long since past. | Legend has it that the crown is made from the bones and teeth of ancient dragons, and is said to increase the power of the wearer. | Whatever the truth, if Ulfric get's his hands on it, it would be a powerful symbol around which to rally support for his cause.

Well, to be frank, we don't. Its location was lost with King Borgas, when the Great Hunt killed him while off on his Alessian campaigns. | [E] Supposedly, his body was brought back to Skyrim and secretly buried with the crown. Knowledge of that location was lost, in the Wars of Succession. | But my agents report that Galmar is pretty damned convinced Korvanjund is the tomb of King Borgas. | I know Galmar. We fought in many wars together. He's not a sentimental man taken to fancy. If he believes the crown is there... he's likely found it.

Node.Caption: CW02AAboutKorvanjundTopic: How do we know the crown is in Korvanjund?

Cell.Text: [S] I need someone I can trust to deliver a message of great import to Jarl Balgruuf of Whiterun.
[S] I need someone I can trust to deliver a message of great import to Jarl Hrongar of Whiterun.

[S] G|We have it on good authority that Ulfric has raised enough men to attack the city of Whiterun. The Jarl, however, refuses the Legion's support. | This missive should convince him. Be aware soldier, these documents contain sensitive intelligence for the Jarl's eyes only.
G|I believe the Legate gave you an order. Why are you standing around here flapping your jaw? Move out!

Node.Caption: MQ103RikkeIntroA2: I think I'd rather be a regular soldier.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Yes. An axe. How long have you been in Skyrim. Give the man my axe. | If he keeps it, I will bide my time. If he returns it to you, it means war.
<<Shared>> Men who understand each other often have no need for words. | There are but a few simple truths behind one warrior giving another his axe. | Balgruuf will know my meaning.
<<Shared>> Men who understand each other often have no need for words. | There are but a few simple truths behind one warrior giving another his axe. | Hrongar will know my meaning.

Node.Caption: CW02AUlfricAxeSayAnything: Should I say anything to him?

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> Keep your wits about you. The Jarl of Whiterun is known for his temper.
